    • getEncryptedFileName

      public String getEncryptedFileName()
      gets the name of the associated encrypted file in the media dir format: "." + [uid without "-"]
      Returns:
      the name of the associated encrypted file

    • getUniquePlainName

      public String getUniquePlainName()
      multiple files may have the same plainFileName (e.g. voice messages on from the iOS app always have the name "recordAudio.m4a")

      thus a unique plain name is generated by prepending 4 digits of the uid

      Returns:
      the unique plain file name

      format: [first 4 digits of UID] + "-" + plainFileName

    • saveFile

      public void saveFile​(MasterKey masterKey, File mediaDir, File outDir) throws IOException
      decrypts and saves the media file
      Parameters:
      masterKey - the master key
      mediaDir - the media dir (see FileStore.mediaDir())
      outDir - the output dir (see FileStore.outputDir())
      Throws:
      IOException - if the associated encrypted file couldn't be found or creating the plain file failed
